    Why variables contribute to this state:                                     
                                                                                
     • main function not found: If main was not defined in the source or not    
       linked due to compilation errors, the linker would not know where to     
       jump. This leads to an invalid entry point.                              
     • No debug symbols: Without symbols, lldb cannot resolve main, start, or   
