     • Invalid instruction pointer (0xffffffffffffffff): This is a common       
       indicator that the CPU tried to execute from a zero or all-ones          
       address, which is impossible. It usually happens when the _start         
       function (from crt0) fails to initialize the program correctly.          
                                                                                
